1. you have 2 option for What you can pass in to a state setter function (e.g.
        `setCount`). What are They?
a. new value of the state (setCount(42)) will return 42
b. callback function - whatever the callback function return == new value of the
state

2. When would you want to pass the first option (from answer above) to the state
setter function?
whenever you DON'T need the pverious value of state to determine What the new
value of state should be

3. When would you want to pass the second option (from answer above) to the
state setter function?
whenever you DO need the pverious value of state to determine What the new
value of state should be

